<p>
<strong>Job Search:</strong>
The Job Ads published on Jobtar are taken automatically from other websites or Jobtar Advertisers. When the Ads are taken from third party websites, Jobtar simply indexes and publishes an extract providing the link to view the full Job Ad published on the site of origin.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Alert and Ads via email:</strong>
By providing an email address, you can register for the "Job Alert" Service and receive email notifications about new jobs that match the search filters you set either during registration or at a later time. In addition to notifying you of new Job Ads, the "Job Alert" Service can provide the reception of direct Ads with relevant job vacancies corresponding to the search filters you set.
You can edit your search filters at any time or request that the Service be discontinued. If the User stops interacting with the links on the Job Alert, the Service will stop automatically after some time.
</p>
<p>
